In this post, we are going to compare two high-profile media players : VidHub and Infuse. While they all have their own advantages and disadvantages, they are all capable of providing users with a high-quality media experience in different scenarios.

# Price advantage: 
VidHub is free to use on all iOS/Mac/tvOS platforms, which saves users a lot of money. In comparison, the price of the Infuse is on the more expensive side, and the buyout requires 698, but the dirt area will be a little more cost-effective.

# Speed
VidHub is known for its fast presentation of information and scraping speed, smooth playback experience, and blazing fast refresh speed. In contrast, Infuse has a slower scanning speed and can be a little inconvenient for users.


# Multiple Platforms Support
VidHub not only supports local directories and network shares, but also makes it easy to mount a variety of domestic and foreign servers: Netdisk, Alibaba Cloud Disk, Premiumize, etc., provide users with more convenient ways to access media.

# Media Library & Emby Standalone Display
VidHub's homepage is clean and clear, and the media library is displayed separately from Emby, avoiding clutter. Some Emby servers may not support Infuse, and Infuse's large cache settings are not adjustable, which may be subject to server rate limiting, while VidHub is not affected by this.

# Fast playback with Emby
Emby's fast playback speed: The new version of VidHub has additional optimizations for Emby's playback speed and loading speed, which will make it feel better than Infuse.

# Powerful
Full features: VidHub provides a lot of handy features such as batch renaming, and users can even use VidHub to rename in batches and then play with Infuse, which greatly enhances the user's operational flexibility

# Fast Response
Fast feedback: VidHub is fast at fixing bugs, and generally problems will be solved in the next version, making the user experience more stable and reliable.

# Variery of Resolution options:
Supports a variety of resolution options: Unlike Infuse, VidHub not only supports original picture playback, but also supports multiple resolution options such as 720P, 480P, P, etc., providing users with more room for choice.

<img width="600" src="data:image/png;base64,"/>

# Pros of Infuse: 
1. Dolby License: Infuse has Dolby Vision and Dolby Atmos licenses on all Apple platforms, providing users with a more powerful audiovisual experience. In contrast, VidHub currently only solves the Dolby color cast problem and does not enable the full Dolby experience.

2. Decoding Advantages: Infuse is even better at decoding, providing higher quality playback for a clearer and smoother viewing experience.

3. Blu-ray playback: Infuse supports Blu-ray playback, providing users with a more diverse media choice.

To summarize, both VidHub and Infuse have their own unique advantages and features. Users can choose according to their needs and preferences to get the best media experience.
